        <updateDate>2016-05-25T21:42:08Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Start Taking Action on Lingering Liabilities Act or the STALL Act</b></p> <p>This bill amends the Federal Trade Commission Act to require certain Federal Trade Commission (FTC) investigations involving civil investigative demands to terminate six months after the FTC sends a verifiable written communication to notify the subject of the investigation. The bill also provides an exception that allows such an investigation to continue beyond that six-month period if, before the period expires, the FTC: (1) sends an additional verifiable written communication, or (2) votes to extend the investigation.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
